      "description": "Available for the discerning enthusiast is this E92 M3, powered by the high-revving S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This power plant features eight individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio, delivering a linear power band up to an 8,400 RPM redline. The longitudinal front-engine, rear-drive layout is complemented by a 6-speed manual transmission and the factory-spec M Variable Differential Lock. This chassis retains the weight-saving carbon fiber roof, effectively lowering the center of gravity. Crucial preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a recent rod bearing service and throttle actuator replacement. The suspension geometry is tight, and the Electronic Damper Control (EDC) provides precise adjustment of the monotube gas-pressure shocks. While the vehicle shows minor aesthetic character consistent with its mileage, the mechanical synchronization and high-induction acoustics remain exceptional.",
